Dialogue: 0,0:00:03.34,0:00:07.69,Dialogue Top,,0,0,0,,{（大滝）いやあ　えらい\Nお世話かけてしもて→\N\Nすいませんでした。}So sorry for having imposed on you like this...
Dialogue: 0,0:00:08.11,0:00:10.69,Dialogue Top,,0,0,0,,{朝飯までごちそうになってもうて。}And even having breakfast at your place...
Dialogue: 0,0:00:10.69,0:00:11.57,Dialogue Top,,0,0,0,,{（毛利小五郎）いえいえ。}It's nothing, really...
Dialogue: 0,0:00:11.57,0:00:15.53,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,{（服部平次）まあ　予想外の→\N\Nハプニングっちゅうことで\N堪忍したってや。}Well, it was due to an unexpected turn of events, after all!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:15.53,0:00:19.37,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}{（コナン）\N《ウソつけ...最初から泊まる気\Nマンマンじゃねえか。→}Liar. You planned on staying over from the start.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:19.37,0:00:22.03,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}{着替え用意してんだから》}You even had a change of clothes ready.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:22.03,0:00:24.42,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,{（和葉）ほな　蘭ちゃん　またな。}All right, Ran{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-chan{\r}, see you later!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:24.42,0:00:25.38,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,{（毛利　蘭）またね～。}Later!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:25.38,0:00:27.81,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Well then, I'll get going as well.{ほな　ワシもこれで...。AO}
Dialogue: 0,0:00:27.81,0:00:30.98,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Please stop by again the next time you're free.{次は仕事ぬきで遊びに来て下さい。\NAO}
Dialogue: 0,0:00:30.98,0:00:33.03,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Will do! Now, please excuse me.{はい　失礼します。へへっ。AO}
Dialogue: 0,0:00:33.88,0:00:34.75,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Oh?{あれ？\NAO}
Dialogue: 0,0:00:34.75,0:00:36.39,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,{ん？大滝はん　どこ行くんや？}Otaki{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-han{\r}, where are you goin'?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:37.11,0:00:38.89,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,{東京駅はこっちやで。}Tokyo Station's this way, y'know?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:38.89,0:00:43.85,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,{ああ　先に帰ってええで。ワシは\Nちょっと野暮用があるさかい。}Ah, you kids can go on home without me. I've got some minor business to take care of over here still.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:45.30,0:00:46.19,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,{ふ～ん...あ　そう。\NAO}I see...
Dialogue: 0,0:00:48.76,0:00:51.99,Flashback,,0,0,0,,{\be10}{（服部平蔵）場所は\N群馬と埼玉の県境。→}The location is on the boundary between Gunma and Saitama prefectures,
Dialogue: 0,0:00:51.99,0:00:54.43,Flashback,,0,0,0,,{\be10}{山奥に建つ洋館や。→}a western-style mansion built in the mountain recesses.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:54.43,0:00:59.35,Flashback,,0,0,0,,{\be10}{そこで明日の夜\N遺産相続の会議があるんやが...→}There, tomorrow night, a meeting will be held to discuss an inheritance.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:59.35,0:01:02.37,Flashback,,0,0,0,,{\be10}{お前　それに\N出席してくれへんか？}Can you attend that meeting for me?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:02.62,0:01:09.59,Character Card,,0,0,0,,Heizō Hattori\NŌsaka Police Superintendent · Heiji's Father
Dialogue: 0,0:01:02.70,0:01:08.33,Flashback,,0,0,0,,{\be10\an8}{依頼主の話やと　被相続人の\Nその館の主人の様子が→}According to the client's story, the person whose will is being discussed, the master of the mansion,
Dialogue: 0,0:01:08.33,0:01:10.71,Flashback,,0,0,0,,{\be10\an8}{えらい異様らしくてのぉ...→}has been exhibiting truly strange behavior.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:10.71,0:01:16.24,Flashback,,0,0,0,,{\be10}{せやから　警察関係者に\Nその話し合いに→}That's why he wants someone from the police {同席して欲しい言うてきてん}to also attend the discussion.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:16.24,0:01:19.47,Flashback,,0,0,0,,{\be10}Well, I don't have a problem with that.{はぁ...そらまあ\Nかまいまへんが\NAO}
Dialogue: 0,0:01:20.02,0:01:24.24,Flashback,,0,0,0,,{\be10}{半年前に　その館の近くの森で\N殺しがあって→}Now there was a killing in the forest near that mansion a half-year ago
Dialogue: 0,0:01:24.24,0:01:32.75,Flashback,,0,0,0,,{\be10}{妙な噂も立ってるらしいから\N無理にとは言わんけど...}and some odd rumors surfaced, so I can't say this is without cause, {出てくれるんやったら\N気ぃつけよ...→}but if you go there for me, do take care...
Dialogue: 0,0:01:33.65,0:01:35.77,Flashback,,0,0,0,,{\be10}{血ぃ吸われんようにな}...that you don't get your blood sucked out.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:35.77,0:01:37.75,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,{（平次）何を吸われるっちゅうねん。}What are you sayin' about bein' sucked?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:39.16,0:01:43.83,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,{さっきから　吸われん吸われんってボソボソ言うてるけど。}You've been muttering "Don't be sucked, don't be sucked" to yourself for a while now.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:43.83,0:01:45.83,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,{（大滝）へ　平ちゃん！？}H-Hei{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-chan{\r}?!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:46.73,0:01:50.09,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,{まさか　女の唇のことと\Nちゃうやろな？}Don't tell me, you're thinking about a woman's lips, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:50.09,0:01:52.37,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,{いつの間に車に？}W-When did you get in here?!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:52.37,0:01:57.09,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,{大滝警部が　さっきガソリンスタンドで\Nトイレに行ったスキにこっそりね。}We snuck in when you went to the toilet at the petrol station earlier, Inspector Otaki.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:57.09,0:01:58.87,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,{気づいてなかった？}Didn't you notice?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:58.87,0:02:01.43,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,{小五郎のおじさんたちも→\N\Nついて来てるんだよ。\N（大滝）ええっ！？}That Uncle Kogoro and the others are following you.{altered line}
Dialogue: 0,0:02:04.35,0:02:06.56,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,{け　けど...何で？}B-But why...?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:06.56,0:02:11.80,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,{そら　大滝はんがコソコソ\N会いに行く女の顔を拝みにや。}They want to gaze upon the face of the woman you're secretly meeting with, Otaki{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-han{\r}!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:11.80,0:02:16.65,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,{けど　まさかこっちに女がおるとは思わへんかったな～。}Though I never thought you'd have a woman over on this side.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:16.65,0:02:19.74,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,{蘭ねえちゃんたちも　ちゃんと\N紹介してほしいって言ってたよ。}Ran{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-neechan{\r} and the others said they wanted to be introduced to her.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:19.74,0:02:23.74,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,{いやぁ～　見せられるような\Nええ女やないんで。}Ah, well, she's not so good-looking as to be shown off to others.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:25.15,0:02:27.40,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,{ふ～ん。だったら教えてくれる？}Then will you tell us?{ja -> dattara}
Dialogue: 0,0:02:27.40,0:02:28.71,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,{どんな事件なの？}What kind of case is it?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:30.47,0:02:35.47,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,{事件なんやろ？俺に内緒っちゅうことは　親父がらみとちゃうか？}It is a case, right? And since you kept it from me, that means it has somethin' to do with ol' Dad, doesn't it?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:39.54,0:02:46.31,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,{いやぁ　実は半年前\Nこれから行く館の近くの森で→\N\N女性の遺体が見つかったんや。}Well, actually, at the mansion I am headed to, half a year ago, a woman's corpse was found in the surrounding woods.{rewritten}
Dialogue: 0,0:02:46.80,0:02:52.44,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,{立てた杭に体を逆さにして\N縛りつけられた無残な格好でな。}She was tied upside-down to a stake that was driven into the ground, in a cruel pose.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:53.06,0:02:55.44,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,{そらまた　エグイのぉ...。}That's harsh.{Added "mata"; not reflected in translation}
Dialogue: 0,0:02:55.85,0:02:59.25,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,{（大滝）\Nその女性は\N館のメイドやったんやけど...→}That lady was employed as the mansion's maid, but...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:59.25,0:03:02.07,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,{遺体の様子が\Nなんや　けったいで...。}Since the appearance of the corpse was really odd...{sono removed; shitai "corpse" replaced with itai}
Dialogue: 0,0:03:03.10,0:03:04.87,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,{けったいって　何がや？}What do you mean by odd?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:05.44,0:03:07.95,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,{その遺体見つけた老夫婦が}The corpse was found by an old couple.{Same shitai/itai change}
Dialogue: 0,0:03:07.95,0:03:14.25,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,{肌の色があんまり白ぉて→}But since her skin was unnaturally white, {最初は　逆さに立てた熊よけの\Nカカシと間違えたみたいで。}at first they mistook her for an upside-down scarecrow intended to ward off bears.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:14.71,0:03:20.25,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,{そんなん　動脈切って\N失血死させて→\N\Nそこに縛ったに\N決まってるやないか。}Wouldn't that just be because she died from blood loss due to a sliced artery, and was tied there?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:20.25,0:03:24.26,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,{けど　そない大きな傷は\Nどこにもなかったらしいんや。}But there weren't any big wounds like that.{Slight change of wording}
Dialogue: 0,0:03:24.83,0:03:29.27,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,{あったんは　首筋にあいてた\N２つの穴だけで...。}The only things were two holes punctured in the nape of her neck.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:30.16,0:03:32.65,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,{首筋に２つの穴で失血死？}Death by blood loss with two holes in the nape of her neck?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:32.65,0:03:35.57,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,{お　おい　それって　まさか...。}H-Hey, that wouldn't be...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:35.57,0:03:36.59,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:36.59,0:03:42.75,Flashback,,0,0,0,,{\be10}{（平蔵の声）\N大滝...お前　この世に\Nおると思うか？吸血鬼...。\NAO}Otaki, do you think vampires exist in this world?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:46.49,0:03:50.70,Narration Off,,0,0,0,,{\be10}Seeking comprehensive answers, he clears all mysteries and codes!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:50.70,0:03:52.58,Narration Off,,0,0,0,,{\be10}Dracula's real?!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:52.58,0:03:54.83,Narration Off,,0,0,0,,{\be10}The curtains open to a shocking case!{＜ドラキュラが実在するって？\N衝撃事件の幕が開く＞}
Dialogue: 0,0:03:54.83,0:03:56.27,Narration Off,,0,0,0,,{\be10}He sees the single truth for what it is,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:56.27,0:03:58.02,Narration Off,,0,0,0,,{\be10}and looks like a kid but has the mind of an adult!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:58.02,0:04:00.88,Narration Off,,0,0,0,,{\be10}His name? Detective Conan!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:48.33,0:05:50.11,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,{きゅ　吸血鬼！？}A-A vampire?!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:50.49,0:05:53.45,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,{その殺し　吸血鬼の仕業だって\N言うんスか！？}Do you mean to say that killing was the work of a vampire?!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:53.45,0:05:56.50,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,{いや～\Nただのしょうもない噂です。}It's just a baseless rumor.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:56.50,0:06:00.12,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,{昔　この辺を　そないな大名が\N治めてはったらしいし。}Since this area used to be governed by a daimyō who was sorta vampire-like.{it's not like daimyō isn't known in English, do we want to leave that translated or detranslate it? "Feudal lord" here}
Dialogue: 0,0:06:00.75,0:06:01.87,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,{ん？大名？}Daimyō?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:02.53,0:06:06.29,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,{ほんで　その殺人犯\Nまだ捕まってないんか？}And? That murderer hasn't been arrested yet?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:06.29,0:06:06.84,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,{ああ...。}Yeah...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:07.25,0:06:09.63,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,{しかし　容疑者ぐらいは\Nいたんじゃ...。}But wasn't there at least a suspect?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:09.63,0:06:15.90,Dialogue Top,,0,0,0,,{ええ　真っ先に疑われたんが\Nこの館の主の寅倉迫弥さんです。}Yeah. The first one to be suspected was the master of the mansion, Hakuya Torakura{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:09.88,0:06:14.97,Character Card,,0,0,0,,Hakuya Torakura (57)\NTorakura Family Head
Dialogue: 0,0:06:15.90,0:06:20.26,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,{殺されたメイドが　館のシェフに\Nもらしてたらしいんですわ。}It seems the murdered maid had confided in the mansion's chef...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:20.26,0:06:22.25,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,{「旦那様が　最近不気味で→}"The master has been acting really weird lately,"
Dialogue: 0,0:06:22.25,0:06:25.56,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,{身の危険を感じるから\Nメイド辞めたい」って。}"and I feel like I'm in danger, so I want to quit being a maid."
Dialogue: 0,0:06:25.56,0:06:27.48,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,{じゃあ　やっぱり主が？}Then as expected, that master...?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:27.86,0:06:29.45,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,{ああ　いや...。}Ah, no...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:29.45,0:06:31.49,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,{（古賀）アリバイがあったんですよ。}He had an alibi.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:32.13,0:06:36.18,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,{メイドの清水さんが亡くなった\N死亡推定時刻に→}At the approximate time that the maid, Shimizu{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}, died,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:36.18,0:06:40.24,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,{旦那様は　ずっと部屋にこもって\N寝てらしたというアリバイが...→}the master had been cooped up in his room sleeping the entire time.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:40.97,0:06:48.25,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,{皮肉にも　それを証言したのは\N清水さんに相談を受けていた→\N\Nそのシェフなんですけどね。}Ironically, the one who testified to that effect was the same chef whom Shimizu{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} had confided in.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:48.92,0:06:53.88,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,{ようこそ　おいで下さいました。大阪府警の大滝警部ですね？}I extend a warm welcome. Inspector Otaki from the Ōsaka police, I presume?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:54.25,0:06:55.65,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,{あ　はい...}Ah, yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:55.65,0:06:57.22,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,{ほんなら　あんたが依頼主の...。}So you must be the client?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:57.51,0:07:03.23,Character Card,,0,0,0,,Rikushige Koga (71)\NTorakura Family Butler
Dialogue: 0,0:06:57.66,0:07:03.25,Dialogue Top,,0,0,0,,{執事の古賀です。服部本部長の\N父上とは　同期の桜でして。}I am Koga, the butler. I was a classmate of Superintendent Hattori's father.{null: Fixed "in the same year year as" -> "a classmate of",}
Dialogue: 0,0:07:03.60,0:07:08.19,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,{ねえ　なんなの？最近の旦那様の\N様子が不気味だったって。}Say, what was it? The "strange behaviour" the master has supposedly been showing lately?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:08.91,0:07:16.04,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,{ああ...近頃の旦那様は→}Oh, recently the master has started {陽を避けるように　昼間はずっと\N部屋で寝てらしたり→}doing things such as sleeping in his room all through the day to try and avoid the sunlight,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:16.04,0:07:23.41,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,{愛用なさっていた食器類も\N自分は銀アレルギーだと→}suddenly throwing out all of his beloved silver tableware, {急に言い出されて\N全てお捨てになったり。}saying that he was allergic to silver...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:23.88,0:07:28.36,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,{先日は　好物のニンニクの入った\Nスープの皿を叩き割られて→}And the other day, he smashed the bowl of his favorite soup with garlic in it into pieces...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:28.36,0:07:32.21,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,{「血が腐るから二度と入れるな」と大層ご立腹で。}He said, "It makes my blood rot, so never use garlic again!", in an extreme rage.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:32.55,0:07:34.72,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,{お　おい　それって　まるで...。}H-Hey, that's almost as if...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:35.09,0:07:36.02,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,{ええ。}Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:36.02,0:07:39.22,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,{メイドの清水さんには\Nそう映ったんでしょう。→}I'm sure to the maid Shimizu{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} it appeared that way.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:39.94,0:07:43.52,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,{まるで吸血鬼...\Nバンパイアのようだと。}As if he had become a vampire.{both manga and anime use "kyuuketsuki, vampire"}
Dialogue: 0,0:07:44.02,0:07:45.39,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,{（和葉・蘭）バ　バンパイア！？}V-Vampire?!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:45.90,0:07:48.61,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,{今　バンパイア言うてへんかった？}Just now, did you just say "vampire"?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:48.61,0:07:50.65,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,{吸血鬼がどうかしたの？}What do vampires have to do with this?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:50.65,0:07:51.27,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,{ああ　いや...。}Ah, that is...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:51.82,0:07:53.23,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,{あ～　あれや！\Nバンパーや　バンパー。}Ah, that's it! He said bumper, bumper!{partial rewrite. pun: bampaia/bampaa}
Dialogue: 0,0:07:53.96,0:07:58.24,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,{レンタカーのバンパーに\N傷つけてしもて→\N\Nどないしょ～言うてたんや。}We're just discussing what to do since the bumper of the rental car got dented!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:58.24,0:08:01.04,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,{な～んだ　バンパーか～。}Oh, so it was "bumper"?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:01.04,0:08:03.86,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,{なあ！平次らも早よ中　入り！}Hey, Heiji{plural not reflected in mangalation}, let's all hurry and go inside!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:03.86,0:08:05.62,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,{お城みたいで　すごいよ。}It's amazing, just like a castle!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:05.62,0:08:07.41,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,{へえ...。}Oh?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:07.93,0:08:13.14,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,{では　そろそろ陽も傾いて\N旦那様が　お目覚めになる頃合い。}Well then, as the sun wanes and the time for the master to rise draws near,{manga o-oki -> anime o-mezame; no difference in translation here}
Dialogue: 0,0:08:13.14,0:08:17.80,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,{夕食の支度がととのうまで\N館内でくつろいでいて下さい。}please relax inside the mansion until the preparations for dinner are complete.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:17.80,0:08:19.09,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,{あ　はい。}Ah, yes, sir.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:20.36,0:08:25.60,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,{問題の遺産相続の話し合いは\N夕食後とのことですので。}For the inheritance discussion in question will take place after dinner...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:26.13,0:08:31.27,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hey, I wonder if Inspector Otaki's darling really is inside this mansion.{ねえ　ホントに　この館の中に→\N\N大滝警部の愛しい人いるのかなあ？}
Dialogue: 0,0:08:31.94,0:08:34.82,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}She {\i1}still{\i0} believes that?{《そのネタ　まだ信じてんのかよ》}
Dialogue: 0,0:08:36.49,0:08:38.11,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,{すごいねえ...→}This is amazing!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:38.56,0:08:43.55,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,{こういうのって映画やドラマで\Nよくあるけど→}I've only ever seen something like this in movies or dramas. To think I'm actually experiencing it!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:43.55,0:08:44.53,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,{（和葉）ホンマ！}You said it.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:45.10,0:08:47.80,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,{アタシらも\N貴族になった気分やわぁ！}It feels like we've also become aristocrats!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:47.80,0:08:48.83,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,{（寅倉瑠莉）誰よ？あんたら。→}Who are you lot?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:50.50,0:08:56.42,Character Card,,0,0,0,,Ruri Torakura (38)\NAsanobu's Wife
Dialogue: 0,0:08:51.10,0:08:54.98,Dialogue Top,,0,0,0,,{まさかアンタたち　お義兄様の\N隠し子とかじゃないでしょうね？}Don't tell me you lot are our brother's illegitimate children, now!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:54.98,0:08:56.68,Dialogue Top,,0,0,0,,{（寅倉麻信）そんなわけないだろ！}There's no way that could be, is there?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:57.71,0:09:01.89,Character Card,,0,0,0,,Asanobu Torakura (52)\NSecond son of the Torakura family
Dialogue: 0,0:08:58.19,0:09:01.89,Dialogue Top,,0,0,0,,{もしそうなら→\N\N兄さんが僕たちを\Nここへ呼ぶわけないし。}If that had been the case, there would have been no reason for Brother to have called us here.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:02.60,0:09:08.06,Dialogue Top,,0,0,0,,That's right. If they really were illegitimate children, Hakuya's inheritance wouldn't go to us, his siblings.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:03.18,0:09:08.06,Character Card,,0,0,0,,Kamiyo Torakura (60)\NFirst-born daughter of the Torakura family
Dialogue: 0,0:09:08.55,0:09:11.54,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The full amount would go to his children.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:11.54,0:09:13.56,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But who knows, eh?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:14.05,0:09:17.28,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,After all, didn't he suddenly bring her here years ago?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:17.28,0:09:20.07,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,His considerably younger, beautiful fiancée.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:20.32,0:09:26.95,Character Card,,0,0,0,,Jōhei Hagawa (29)\NKamiyo's Lover
Dialogue: 0,0:09:20.84,0:09:24.01,Dialogue Top,,0,0,0,,It wouldn't be strange at all if he had two or three illegitimate children, you know.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:24.39,0:09:27.83,Dialogue Top,,0,0,0,,Well, that fiancée unfortunately died soon after.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:28.22,0:09:31.84,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Oh, I see. That was pretty lucky for you guys, wasn't it?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:31.84,0:09:32.85,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,H-Hey...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:35.13,0:09:39.72,Character Card,,0,0,0,,Kishiharu Tarakura (45)\NThird Son of the Torakura Family
Dialogue: 0,0:09:35.24,0:09:39.72,Dialogue Top,,0,0,0,,Watch it! If you keep going on about it again, you won't be laughing at the end!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:40.47,0:09:42.02,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,W-What?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:42.02,0:09:44.51,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I'm sure you thought it was a stroke of luck, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:45.18,0:09:51.27,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Oh, what's this? Could it be that you and that mistress-with-kids really had an affair or something?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:51.67,0:09:53.62,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,W-Why, you...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:53.62,0:09:56.19,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Can we stop talking about mistresses?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:56.94,0:09:59.69,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,After all, I was a child born from Father's mistress.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:59.90,0:10:07.08,Character Card,,0,0,0,,Mina Torakura (26)\NSecond daughter of the Torakura family
Dialogue: 0,0:10:00.31,0:10:04.98,Dialogue Top,,0,0,0,,Well, legally speaking, if there aren't any heirs besides siblings,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:04.98,0:10:09.30,Dialogue Top,,0,0,0,,the inheritance would be equally divided. So let's all get along.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:09.30,0:10:10.15,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Umm...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:11.20,0:10:17.17,Character Card,,0,0,0,,Hikaru Hinohara (24)\NTorakura Family Maid
Dialogue: 0,0:10:11.40,0:10:15.40,Dialogue Top,,0,0,0,,The chef asked me to come and see if it'd be okay with everyone if he started serving now.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:15.40,0:10:19.59,Dialogue Top,,0,0,0,,But if you're not done with your conversation, I'll tell him to wait a bit.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:20.12,0:10:24.22,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,We can still talk while we're eating, so go ahead and bring out the food!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:24.22,0:10:29.82,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Either way, since you're just his wife's son, it has no bearing on you.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:29.82,0:10:34.05,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,This is shapin' up to be some inheritance battle.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:34.05,0:10:34.94,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I know, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:37.47,0:10:38.44,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,An incurable illness?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:40.40,0:10:43.60,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hakuya Torakura{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}, the master of this household, is terminally ill?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:43.60,0:10:46.48,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah. He has half a year or so left.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:46.48,0:10:48.83,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Oh? Wasn't it three months?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:49.49,0:10:52.78,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's why we came to this dinner party, you know.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:52.78,0:10:57.79,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Well, the invitation said "if you don't attend, you won't receive any inheritance", after all.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:58.66,0:11:00.95,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,On that note, isn't Brother late?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:00.95,0:11:04.76,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You're right. At this point, he'd usually be complaining about the food.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:05.28,0:11:10.05,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Sorry to ask you this, but could you two girls go and wake him up?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:10.05,0:11:11.10,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Wait, us?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:11.53,0:11:14.95,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If you turn right at the hallway, it's the last room.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:14.95,0:11:19.45,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Good idea. Hakuya might be in a better mood if he's woken up by young ladies.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:20.76,0:11:24.11,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Umm, he said the last room...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:24.55,0:11:25.45,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Must be this one, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:26.23,0:11:28.41,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But don't you think it's weird?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:28.41,0:11:31.37,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Would you normally ask guests to do this kind of thing?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:33.20,0:11:33.70,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:34.54,0:11:35.87,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,There ain't any bed.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:36.95,0:11:38.12,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Wh—\hNo way!{null: was "Wa- No way!", but sounds like the first part is a cut off "chotto"}
Dialogue: 0,0:11:38.63,0:11:39.48,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,A coffin?!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:39.48,0:11:41.13,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Oh, I see!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:41.76,0:11:46.60,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,When they had us go to wake him, I thought everyone was smirkin'...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:46.60,0:11:50.80,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,They were tryin' to scare us by makin' us see this old guy sleepin' inside a coffin!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:50.80,0:11:54.39,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You shouldn't get inside one of these things before you die!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:08.48,0:12:10.03,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What is it? What happened?!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:10.52,0:12:12.37,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,T-The old man inside is—
Dialogue: 0,0:12:15.77,0:12:17.75,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He's just sleeping.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:17.75,0:12:21.42,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I'm sure Brother sleeps there lately because he figures he'll end up there eventually.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:21.95,0:12:24.71,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But he had blood all over him and there was a stake stabbed in his chest!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:25.24,0:12:26.89,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,B-Blood?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:26.89,0:12:29.10,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Brother really went overboard with the joke this time.{null: fixed, previous line started with "Bro, you've really"}
Dialogue: 0,0:12:29.10,0:12:31.93,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's no joke —\hhe was really dead!{null: Fixed. Previously "It's no joke —\hthere really was a corpse in there!"}
Dialogue: 0,0:12:32.48,0:12:34.05,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}What's with this?!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:34.05,0:12:34.85,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It won't open!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:39.14,0:12:40.85,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The old man ain't in here?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:41.38,0:12:42.23,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,No way!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:42.78,0:12:45.04,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Was he really in here?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:45.04,0:12:47.24,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yes, I'm sure he was...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:48.10,0:12:50.91,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}Then are you sayin' he turned into fog and disappeared?!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:52.50,0:12:54.44,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}As if he was some sort of monster...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:01.00,0:13:02.74,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That can't be!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:02.74,0:13:04.87,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The old man really was lyin' inside the coffin!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:05.35,0:13:09.78,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He had a stake stabbed into his chest, blood all over, was wearin' a black cloak...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:09.78,0:13:12.61,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,...and had long pointy ears and fang-like teeth!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:12.61,0:13:14.06,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Almost as if...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:14.06,0:13:16.26,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,...he was Count Dracula himself!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:16.79,0:13:18.01,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}He looked like...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:18.41,0:13:20.01,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}...Count Dracula?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:20.40,0:13:25.76,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Come to think of it, Brother had that nickname since he was a child.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:25.76,0:13:28.85,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hakuya Torakura becomes Count Dracula?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:25.76,0:13:28.86,Signs,,0,0,0,,dorakyura
Dialogue: 0,0:13:25.76,0:13:28.86,Signs,,0,0,0,,hakushaku
Dialogue: 0,0:13:28.86,0:13:30.77,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,A pretty childish nickname, huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:31.35,0:13:36.62,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But, that nickname might not just be a pun on his name, you know.{null: Removed the first "you know" to avoid redundancy}
Dialogue: 0,0:13:36.62,0:13:39.28,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If you consider the Torakura family ancestors...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:39.80,0:13:41.22,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You're right.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:41.22,0:13:45.73,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And if you add Hakuya's mysterious behavior as of late...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:45.73,0:13:49.35,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Maybe he {\i1}did{\i0} get possessed...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:50.05,0:13:51.04,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,...by a vampire.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:52.88,0:13:55.08,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,She's joking, she's joking.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:55.08,0:13:59.11,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Brother's ears aren't pointy, and he doesn't have fangs.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:59.11,0:14:06.31,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If you two saw Brother like that, then he probably just dressed up as a monster to scare you.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:06.31,0:14:09.40,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Though I don't know what trick he used to disappear from that coffin.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:09.96,0:14:13.23,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Well, magically disappearing in an instant...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:13.86,0:14:17.49,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You typically see vampires doing that in movies and whatnot, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:18.87,0:14:21.80,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Are you trying to treat Brother as a monster?{null: Changed from "Are you trying to turn Brother into a monster?"}
Dialogue: 0,0:14:21.80,0:14:25.07,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I'm not the only one who thinks that.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:25.07,0:14:26.70,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Right, Mr. Butler?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:26.70,0:14:30.33,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You thought so too —\hthat's why you brought these people here, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:30.33,0:14:31.50,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Y-Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:32.15,0:14:36.64,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Since the master's behavior has been rather odd as of late,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:37.35,0:14:43.05,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I asked these police detectives to be present during the inheritance discussion.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:43.62,0:14:44.81,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,P-Police detectives?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:44.81,0:14:47.71,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I'm Otaki, from the Ōsaka Police.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:47.71,0:14:50.19,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And this is the private detective, Kogoro Mouri{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:50.73,0:14:51.27,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,No way!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:51.27,0:14:53.19,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You wouldn't be Sleeping Kogoro?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:53.55,0:14:54.68,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The one and only!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:54.68,0:14:55.48,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Umm...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:56.77,0:15:00.11,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The meal's gone cold, so should I heat it up again?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:01.05,0:15:05.04,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hey, Otaki{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-han{\r}, sorry for buttin' in, but...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:05.04,0:15:08.00,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Can you swab this red spot in the coffin and have the nearby police examine it?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:09.76,0:15:15.92,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If it's like Kazuha said, this should be Hakuya{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}'s blood.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:20.36,0:15:24.08,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,In the end, Brother-in-law never showed up.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:24.08,0:15:27.43,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Well, the invitation said the discussion was {\i1}after{\i0} dinner.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:28.16,0:15:31.44,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Well, he never said the discussion would be in the dining room, though.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:32.55,0:15:34.94,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hey, Conan{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r}. Dad's not around, is he?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:36.11,0:15:40.44,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Uncle took the car with Inspector Otaki to buy cigarettes.{null: Anime added "車に乗ってた"}
Dialogue: 0,0:15:41.25,0:15:43.95,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hey, want to get that photo over and done with?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:45.09,0:15:46.33,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What photo?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:46.33,0:15:51.61,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,When the family gathers up like this, we always take a photo together.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:51.61,0:15:53.67,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It started three generations ago.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:54.32,0:15:58.05,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But are you gonna take the photo even though the master ain't here?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:58.61,0:16:05.16,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah. When we were taking the photo last year, Brother suddenly popped into the room and said "Include me!", so...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:05.16,0:16:05.88,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:06.66,0:16:12.06,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If we all sound like we're enjoying ourselves, Brother might suddenly show up.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:15.08,0:16:17.01,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Mina, lift your chin a little.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:17.86,0:16:20.15,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hey, Sis! Are you gonna stop messing with your hair?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:20.75,0:16:22.95,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You're not gonna get any younger no matter how long you mess with it!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:22.95,0:16:24.82,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Oh, hush, you.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:24.82,0:16:26.33,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Don't worry.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:26.33,0:16:27.70,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You're still beautiful, honey.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:28.52,0:16:29.86,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Thanks.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:29.86,0:16:35.07,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Okay, when I get in place over there, please push this shutter button.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:35.07,0:16:35.96,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Okay.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:38.56,0:16:40.59,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Get ready, everyone!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:41.22,0:16:41.84,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,All right!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:41.84,0:16:42.26,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Chee—
Dialogue: 0,0:16:48.75,0:16:49.68,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What are you yellin' about?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:50.43,0:16:53.18,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Just now, behind everyone...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:53.88,0:16:56.56,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The old man from the coffin was...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:59.20,0:16:59.90,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Where is he?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:00.48,0:17:02.65,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He was there just then...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:02.65,0:17:05.33,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Between Jōhei{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} and Kamiyo{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:05.33,0:17:08.03,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,With a pale face, floating as if he were a ghost...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:08.43,0:17:11.54,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah! What I saw gave off that kind of feeling, too!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:12.15,0:17:15.68,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Will you two stop that already?!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:15.68,0:17:20.72,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I'm sure you came with those detectives because you heard all about the uproar over vampires,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:20.72,0:17:25.42,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,but don't go screaming at some imaginary thing like you're in a haunted house!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:26.60,0:17:28.20,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Uproar over vampires?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:28.20,0:17:28.80,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What's that about?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:29.32,0:17:32.35,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Huh? You really don't know?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:32.35,0:17:35.80,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Half a year ago, in the woods near this mansion,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:35.80,0:17:39.85,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Shimizu{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}, who'd been employed here as a maid, was found dead.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:40.72,0:17:46.32,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,All the blood from her body had been drained, and she'd been tied upside-down to a stake that had been driven into the ground.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:48.27,0:17:53.24,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,To make things worse, there were two holes in the body's neck, so there was a huge commotion.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:53.24,0:17:55.08,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Everyone was saying "vampire"!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:55.68,0:17:59.00,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Anyway, we should split up and look for Brother.{null: Previously: "Anyway, if this goes on,"}
Dialogue: 0,0:17:59.00,0:18:02.96,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,At this rate, he could turn out to be a monster for real!{null: previously "Brother really will be made into a monster!"}
Dialogue: 0,0:18:03.44,0:18:04.92,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Heiji, is this for real?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:04.92,0:18:07.47,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That story about the vampire...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:07.47,0:18:07.47,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:08.56,0:18:11.74,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If we'd told you girls, you'd have wanted to go home right away,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:11.74,0:18:16.14,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,and we figured we'd have to go home with you too, so we kept quiet.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:16.75,0:18:18.10,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What? They're gone.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:19.02,0:18:19.65,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Over there.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:21.09,0:18:22.56,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hey, you two! Where are you going?!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:25.75,0:18:28.28,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You want to eat something with garlic?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:28.88,0:18:31.71,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But didn't you just eat dinner?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:31.71,0:18:33.28,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But there wasn't any garlic in it!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:33.28,0:18:37.79,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If you just let us use this kitchen and the ingredients, we can make the food ourselves!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:38.67,0:18:43.28,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But lately, the master has taken to dislike garlic,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:43.28,0:18:44.71,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,so I don't know if we even have any.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:45.15,0:18:46.80,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Don't trouble yourself.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:46.80,0:18:48.54,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,We'll look for it ourselves.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:50.23,0:18:52.76,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Garlic to ward off vampires, huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:52.76,0:18:54.39,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Well, it's standard.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:54.80,0:18:57.77,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Huh? This fridge won't open.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:58.37,0:19:02.75,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Oh, that's a fridge the master just bought and had installed.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:02.75,0:19:04.27,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's locked.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:04.87,0:19:06.45,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,A locked fridge?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:06.45,0:19:07.45,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Why?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:07.45,0:19:08.47,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I dunno.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:08.47,0:19:16.79,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I heard it was supposed to have some fine meat for tonight's guests, but in the end, it wasn't used, huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:19.10,0:19:19.70,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hey...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:20.36,0:19:21.78,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Was it you?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:22.58,0:19:27.62,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Were you the one who testified in the case half a year ago that the master had an alibi?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:27.62,0:19:28.71,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Y-Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:29.38,0:19:32.97,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If I recall, you said the master had been cooped up in his room sleeping the whole time.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:33.57,0:19:36.42,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah, I'm sure about it.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:36.42,0:19:39.81,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He wanted to sample the soup as soon as he woke up that day,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:39.81,0:19:43.27,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,so he told me, the chef, to bring it to him and wake him up as soon as it was ready.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:43.92,0:19:49.38,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,So then, you weren't watchin' the coffin the whole time, were you?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:49.38,0:19:52.65,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,No, but there's no way he'd have come out.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:53.63,0:19:58.95,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Before he closed the lid on the coffin, he said that he felt like somebody'd been opening its lid{null: removed "the coffin's" for redundance}
Dialogue: 0,0:19:58.95,0:20:01.55,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,and looking at his sleeping face recently.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:01.55,0:20:04.02,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,So he asked if I could put something on top of the lid.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:04.95,0:20:08.09,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Therefore, I put three sesame seeds on top of the lid.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:08.92,0:20:12.80,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And when I came to wake him up, they were just where I'd left them.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:12.80,0:20:15.14,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That means the coffin's lid hadn't been opened, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:20.92,0:20:26.06,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Which means that this coffin is what's suspicious, but...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:26.06,0:20:30.03,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,There don't seem to be any gaps in the tiles under the coffin.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:30.03,0:20:30.90,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:31.88,0:20:34.63,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But why was the lid closed?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:34.63,0:20:37.16,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The lid only opens this far.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:37.85,0:20:42.91,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Normally, when someone sees a corpse, they get surprised and let go of the lid.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:45.02,0:20:49.68,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,No, I mean, when we first tried to open the lid, it wouldn't open, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:49.68,0:20:50.71,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You're right...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:51.63,0:20:55.19,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Plus, for some reason, this room gives me an uneasy feeling.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:57.55,0:20:59.22,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What was that sound?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:59.99,0:21:01.52,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It sounded pretty far away.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:04.10,0:21:05.31,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hey, look at that!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:05.85,0:21:08.11,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The forest's on fire!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:09.87,0:21:10.77,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,A cave-in?!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:11.41,0:21:14.78,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You're sayin' that the tunnel collapsed due to an unexplained explosion?!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:15.35,0:21:19.28,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yes, that's what I was told when I called to find out earlier.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:19.28,0:21:22.66,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You've got to be kidding me! That's the only road here!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:23.18,0:21:25.85,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It seems it'll take some time before it's restored.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:25.85,0:21:29.17,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Geez, this isn't the time to be searching for Brother.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:29.85,0:21:32.59,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Then the master hasn't been found yet?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:32.59,0:21:35.42,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,No, even though we split up to look for him.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:36.04,0:21:39.48,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,By the way, has anyone seen my honey?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:39.48,0:21:41.07,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I haven't seen her for a while.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:41.97,0:21:44.02,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Now that you mention it, I haven't seen Kishiharu{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-niisan{\r} either.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:44.72,0:21:49.52,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Well, Kishiharu said he was going to try and develop the photo we took earlier,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:49.52,0:21:51.52,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,so he made his room into a darkroom.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:52.01,0:21:55.85,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Using an analog camera in this day and age is pretty rare, though.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:55.85,0:21:58.20,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Sorry for being an analog freak.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:58.90,0:22:02.85,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But thanks to that, I know what happened to our brother.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:02.85,0:22:05.08,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Huh? You found Brother?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:05.50,0:22:07.54,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah. He's here in the photo.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:08.07,0:22:09.75,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,In the photo?!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:11.48,0:22:17.88,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Like the girls said, he was right next to us in the room where we took the picture.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:18.71,0:22:22.58,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Having been reduced into a monster that can slip through walls...
Dialogue: 0,0:23:45.36,0:23:48.95,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Why is Brother-in-law in this photo when he wasn't there at the time?!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:49.57,0:23:53.29,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I'm certain they should've been able to see the master there at that time.{null: I think it's あの時そこに旦那様が見えたって事が確かと思うよ。}
Dialogue: 0,0:23:53.86,0:23:57.79,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The blood found inside the the coffin the master slept in really {\i1}was{\i0} type AB?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:58.39,0:24:05.59,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Counting those associated with this mansion, I believe the only one with type AB was the maid Shimizu{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}, who died half a year ago.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:08.97,0:24:14.98,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,On the next Conan: Heiji Hattori and the Vampire Mansion (Two)!
Dialogue: 0,0:24:14.98,0:24:19.90,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Next Conan's Hint: Garlic!
Dialogue: 0,0:24:20.27,0:24:21.60,Dialogue Top,,0,0,0,,Hattori, what are you looking for?
Dialogue: 0,0:24:21.60,0:24:23.42,Dialogue Top,,0,0,0,,Garlic, a cross and a silver spoon!{null: Missing the last bit of "大蒜と十字架と銀の?と"}
Dialogue: 0,0:24:23.42,0:24:24.42,Dialogue Top,,0,0,0,,Hey, calm down!
